Sorry, but you're both wrong. Best practice is this:<p><pre><code>  (function($) {
      // Plugin code
  }) (jQuery)
</code></pre>
And you'll see it in UI and most other good jQuery plugins.

Yeah, but that's really clunky when you want to do<p><pre><code>    @this
    @that
    @the_other
    def foo(self):
        frobnicate()
</code></pre>
This is what Java people call "aspect oriented programming" and get all excited about, but to us it's no big deal :-)
